# Coming Soon Live

A standalone Shopify Online Store 2.0 theme for splash pages, live streaming, and boutique-style merchandising. This repository is self-contained: deploy it directly to a store without forking upstream theme repositories or signing third-party contributor agreements.

## Features

- Coming soon and splash landing pages with email capture
- Live stream sections (self-hosted via optional `streaming/` stack or external HLS URLs)
- 3D boutique and catalog splash experiences
- Full storefront support: products, collections, cart, blog, and customer accounts

## Requirements

- [Shopify CLI](https://shopify.dev/docs/api/shopify-cli) 3.x or later
- A Shopify store (development or production) with staff or collaborator access

Install the CLI globally:

```bash
npm install -g @shopify/cli@latest
```

## Deploy

1. Clone this repository and change into the theme directory (theme files live at the repo root).

2. Authenticate with your store:

```bash
shopify auth login
```

3. Push the theme (unpublished by default):

```bash
shopify theme push --unpublished
```

To publish after review:

```bash
shopify theme publish --theme <theme-id>
```

## Local development

Start a development server with hot reload:

```bash
shopify theme dev --store <your-store.myshopify.com>
```

Lint the theme without store credentials:

```bash
shopify theme check
```

## Repository layout

| Path | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `assets/` | CSS, JavaScript, and static images |
| `config/` | Theme settings schema and defaults |
| `layout/` | Base HTML layouts |
| `locales/` | Translation strings |
| `sections/` | Theme sections (including custom splash/stream sections) |
| `snippets/` | Reusable Liquid partials |
| `templates/` | JSON templates for pages, products, collections |
| `streaming/` | Optional Docker stack for self-hosted live streams (excluded from Shopify uploads via `.shopifyignore`) |

## Custom page templates

- `page.coming-soon.json` — Coming soon landing
- `page.splash-streams.json` — Splash streams hub
- `product.splash.json` / `product.classic.json` — Product layouts
- `collection.splash-streams.json` — Stream collection layout

Configure stream URLs and posters in the theme editor under the relevant section settings.

## Optional live streaming stack

The `streaming/` directory contains a MediaMTX + Caddy Docker Compose setup for self-hosted WebRTC/HLS. It is not required for theme development; sections degrade gracefully when no stream URL is set.

